              "type": "ReferenceGroup",
              "primaryrefs": [
                {
                  "type": "Reference",
                  "refclass": "A",
                  "comment": "Aramaic is a language related to Hebrew, known from Assyrian times. Under the influence of the Persian empire Aramaic was the diplomatic language in later OT times. In Palestine, by the time of the NT, it was spoken widely, having largely displaced Hebrew as the everyday language of the Jews.",
